Hawaiian Airlines Inc said it willcontinue to expand services to Pacific Islands this year.    The company said it will increase its South Pacificservices to daily service, from the current four flights perweek, and beginning May 21 it will fly twice a week to theWestern Pacific to Guam.    Hawaiian Airlines also said it has applied with theDepartment of Transportation for an emergency exemption toprovide service to Tahiti, with connecting services to AmericanSamoa, New Zealand and Cooke Islands. Reuter&#3;